cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a new random access scheme for wireless networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper utilizes the concept of signal-to-interference-plus-noise-ratio (SINR) to improve the random access scheme, which is a key concept in information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The proposed scheme involves adapting the transmit probability based on local information, which can be seen as a control system. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The proposed scheme can potentially improve the performance of multimedia applications in wireless networks by reducing collisions and improving throughput. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although not the main focus of the paper, the proposed scheme can have implications for security in wireless networks by reducing the likelihood of eavesdropping and interference.
